ScriptName FindHolesVecMakeNavItemAndComb
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Summary (one line):
# Detect holes on the current map, optionally apply the map item’s stored hole-vector geometry, create Navigator points at the holes, then combine them into Multiple Records (Multi-shot) groups.
#
# What it does (overview):
# 1) FindHoles
#    - Runs SerialEM’s hole-finding on the currently active map/buffer using the current hole-finding settings.
#    - Result: a list of hole positions becomes available for subsequent commands.
#
# 2) UseMapItemHoleVectors -1
#    - Tells SerialEM to use “hole vectors” associated with a Navigator Map item.
#    - The argument “-1” usually means “use the current/active map item” (i.e., the map you are working on now).
#    - Effect: hole pattern geometry (spacing/orientation) can be taken from the map item’s stored vectors instead of re-deriving it each time.
#
# 3) MakeNavPointsAtHoles 0 -999999 -999999 -1
#    - Converts the detected holes into actual Navigator points.
#    - The exact meaning of the arguments depends on SerialEM’s command definition, but the intent is:
#      - create points at all found holes,
#      - use default / “no limit” options (the -999999 values are commonly used as “don’t constrain” sentinels),
#      - and apply to the current map item (the final -1).
#    - Result: new Navigator entries (points) appear at hole positions.
#
# 4) CombineHolesToMulti 0
#    - Combines the created hole points into “Multiple Records” acquisition groups (multi-shot per hole).
#    - The “0” commonly indicates using current Multiple Records settings / default combine behavior.
#    - Result: Navigator points are grouped so that acquisition will run multiple shots per hole using SerialEM’s Multi-shot logic.
#
# Notes / things to watch:
# - This script assumes the current map is already selected/loaded and the hole-finding parameters are appropriate for that map magnification and grid type.
# - If FindHoles fails (bad contrast / wrong binning / wrong hole size), downstream steps will still run but may create no points.
# - “UseMapItemHoleVectors” is only useful if the map item actually has valid hole vectors stored; otherwise it may have no effect.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

FindHoles 
UseMapItemHoleVectors -1
MakeNavPointsAtHoles 0 -999999 -999999 -1 
CombineHolesToMulti 0
EndMacro
